{
  "stem": "7069.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When eventually I was thrown out of school at age 14, when the principal called me and said that I should go home, pack my stuff, that Jewish kids are not allowed to be in public school anymore.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I was not too unhappy at that point.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My brother-- not at that moment.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My brother was at the university-- and at the university and studied his languages.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was really brilliant.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He speaks nine languages.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he was one of the very last Jewish students on the university that-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] that were allowed to be there.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a Berliner university, the Berlin University.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At that-- I don't know if there was any other name involved in the-- at this moment.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, the night of November 9th to 10th, to the 10th, was the famous or infamous Kristallnacht, The Night of Broken Glass, as it is know, or Crystal Night.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was the night where, during that night, almost all synagogues in Germany, as well as in Austria-- which by that time had been annexed by Hitler-- were destroyed by fire or explosions, or what have you.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I remember that we were ready to go to bed the night of the ninth.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Of course, first of all, let me go back.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It started on November 8th, when a-- a young Jewish student, living with his uncle in Paris, a-- a-- a German from Polish-- of Polish descent, a young Jewish student, spending some time with his uncle in Paris, going there to school.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When on that day, he went to-- into the Embassy and shot, point blank, one of the German officials, a fellow by the name of vom Rath.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He did that.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
